Report queries joined former output 184 non missing values variable copd new query dataset composed 5 missing values variable age.  report_title customize title summary queries, can use report_title argument: Missing COPD values baseline event default title summary “Report queries” changed “Missing COPD values baseline event”.  report_zeros default, function report, summary queries, variables least one query omit zero queries. include omitted variables summary, can use report_zeros argument: Report queries variable age reported summary spite queries identified.  by_dag REDCap project Data Access Groups (DAGs), might interest report summary one DAGs. , can use by_dag argument: Now can choose see report specific DAG, example, summary generated queries Hospital 2: Report queries DAG, 3 values age bigger 60 2 missing values variable copd.  link easier way access query REDCap output function. using link argument specify domain, REDCap version, project ID event ID, function add column $queries element output direct link REDCap query can found. Note: link work user access project least data viewing rights. can find information domain, REDCap version project ID link Project Home project REDCap:  identifiers events can exported : Project Setup < Define Events  information, pass list link argument: output function now additional column link respective query: can go straight specific query copying pasting link web browser choice.
code: example<- rd_query(covican_transformed,                    variables = c("copd"),                    variables_names = c("Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (Yes/No)"),                    expression = c("is.na(x)"),                    query_name = c("COPD is a missing value."),                    instrument = c("Admission"),                    event = "baseline_visit_arm_1") example <- rd_query(covican_transformed,                     variables = "copd",                     expression = "is.na(x)",                     negate = TRUE,                     event = "baseline_visit_arm_1")  # Printing results example$results example2 <- rd_query(covican_transformed,                      variables = "age",                      expression = "is.na(x)",                      event = "baseline_visit_arm_1",                      addTo = example)  # Printing results example2$results example <- rd_query(covican_transformed,                     variables = c("copd", "age"),                     expression = c("is.na(x)", "x<20"),                     event = "baseline_visit_arm_1",                     report_title = "Missing COPD values in the baseline event")  # text: process identifying queries complete, typical approach adress modifying original dataset REDCap re-run query identification process generating new query dataset. check_queries() function compares previous query dataset new one using arguments old new, respectively. output remains list 2 items, data frame containing information query now additional column (“Modification”) indicating queries new, modified, corrected, remain unchanged. Besides, summary show number queries one categories: Comparison report 7 queries pending resolution, 4 solved queries, 1 miscorrected query, 1 new query previous new query dataset. Note: “Miscorrected” category includes queries belong combination record identifier variable old new reports, different reason. instance, variable missing value old report, new report shows value outside established range, classified “Miscorrected”. title: REDCap Data Management
text: REDCapDM R package allows users manage data exported directly REDCap API connection. package includes several functions designed preprocessing data, generating reports queries like outliers missing values, performing follow-identified query. ‘REDCap’ (Research Electronic Data CAPture; https://projectredcap.org) web application developed Vanderbilt University, designed creating managing online surveys databases. REDCap API serves interface allowing external applications connect REDCap remotely, used programmatically retrieve modify project data settings within REDCap, importing exporting data. REDCapDM website describes package functions.

code: rd_query(   ...,   variables = NA,   expression = NA,   negate = FALSE,   event = NA,   filter = NA,   addTo = NA,   variables_names = NA,   query_name = NA,   instrument = NA,   report_title = NA,   report_zeros = FALSE,   by_dag = FALSE,   link = list(),   data = NULL,   dic = NULL,   event_form = NULL )

title: Identification of queries — rd_query
text: ... List containing data, dictionary event (required). may output `redcap_data` function. variables Character vector names database variables checked. expression Character vector expressions applied selected variables. negate Logical value indicates whether defined expression negated. Defaults `FALSE`. event name REDCap event analyzed. events REDCap project, use argument order name event defined variables belong. filter filter applied dataset. example, branching logic determined variable can applied using argument. addTo Data frame corresponding previous query data frame can add new query data frame. default, function always generates new data frame without taking account previous reports. variables_names Character vector containing description selected variable. default, function automatically takes description variable dictionary REDCap project. query_name Description query. can defined one variables, can define different one variable. default, function defines `value [value] [expression]'`. instrument REDCap's instrument variables belong. can defined one variables, can define different one variable. default, function automatically selects corresponding instrument variable dictionary REDCap project. report_title Character string specifying title report. report_zeros Logical. `TRUE`, function returns report containing variables zero queries. by_dag Logical. `TRUE`, elements output grouped data access groups (DAGs) REDCap project. link List containing project information used create web link query. data Data frame containing data read REDCap. list given, argument required. dic Data frame containing dictionary read REDCap. list given, argument required. event_form Data frame containing correspondence event form. list specified argument necessary.

what: Transformation of the raw data — rd_transform
title: Transformation of the raw data — rd_transform
text: Function transforms raw data REDCap read function `redcap_data`. returns transformed data dictionary along summary results step.

title: Transformation of the raw data — rd_transform
code: rd_transform(   ...,   data = NULL,   dic = NULL,   event_form = NULL,   checkbox_labels = c("No", "Yes"),   checkbox_na = FALSE,   exclude_recalc = NULL,   exclude_to_factor = NULL,   delete_vars = NULL,   delete_pattern = c("_complete", "_timestamp"),   final_format = "raw",   which_event = NULL,   which_form = NULL,   wide = NULL )

title: Transformation of the raw data — rd_transform
text: ... Output function `redcap_data`, list containing data frames data, dictionary event_form (needed) REDCap project. data Data frame containing data read REDCap. list specified argument necessary. dic Data frame  containing dictionary read REDCap. list specified argument necessary. event_form Data frame containing correspondence event form. list specified argument necessary. checkbox_labels Character vector names two options every checkbox variable. Default `c('', 'Yes')`. checkbox_na Logical indicating values checkboxes branching logic set missing branching logic missing (set false) also branching logic satisfied (set true). default false. exclude_recalc Character vector names variables recalculated. Might useful projects calculated fields time consuming recalculation. exclude_to_factor Character vector names variables transformed factors. delete_vars Character vector specifying variables exclude. delete_pattern Character vector specifying regex pattern contain variables exclude. default, variables ending `_complete` `_timestamp` removed. final_format Character string indicating final arrangement format data function return. Choose one `raw`, `by_event` `by_form`. `raw` (default) return transformed data original structure. `by_event` return transformed data nested data frame event. `by_form` return transformed data nested data frame form. which_event Character string indicating one event returned final format selected `by_event`. which_form Character string indicating one form returned final format selected `by_form`. wide Logical indicating data split form (selected) wide format long one.

title: Recalculate REDCap calculated fields — recalculate
text: Function recalculates every calculated field logic can transcribed R. Recall calculated fields smart-variables logic variables events transcribed. function return dataset dictionary added recalculated variables (name calculated field + `_recalc`) along table shows summary results.

title: Recalculate REDCap calculated fields — recalculate
code: recalculate(data, dic, event_form = NULL, exclude_recalc = NULL)

title: Recalculate REDCap calculated fields — recalculate
text: data Data frame containing data REDCap. dic Data frame  containing dictionary read REDCap. event_form Data frame  containing correspondence event form. exclude_recalc Character vector names variables recalculated. Might useful projects calculated fields time consuming recalculation.

title: Read REDCap data — redcap_data
text: function allows users read datasets REDCap project R analysis, either via export data via API connection. REDCap API interface allows communication REDCap server without going interactive REDCap interface.

title: Read REDCap data — redcap_data
code: redcap_data(   data_path = NA,   dic_path = NA,   event_path = NA,   uri = NA,   token = NA,   filter_field = NA )

title: Read REDCap data — redcap_data
text: data_path Character string pathname R file read dataset . dic_path Character string pathname dictionary. event_path Character string pathname file containing correspondence event form (can downloaded `Designate Instruments Events` tab inside `Project Setup` section REDCap) uri URI (Uniform Resource Identification) REDCap project. token Character vector generated token. filter_field Character vector fields REDCap project desired import R (API connection )<.

title: Read REDCap data — redcap_data
text: List containing dataset dictionary REDCap project. event_path specified, also contain third element correspondence events & forms project.

title: Read REDCap data — redcap_data
text: give use package, advise use argument 'dic_path' read dictionary, functions need order run properly. read exported data, must first use REDCap's 'Export Data' function select 'R Statistical Software' format. generate CSV file observations R file necessary code complete variable's information.

title: Read REDCap data — redcap_data
code: if (FALSE) { # Exported files from REDCap  dataset <- redcap_data(data_path = "C:/Users/username/example.r",                        dic_path = "C:/Users/username/example_dictionary.csv",                        event_path = "C:/Users/username/events.csv")  # API connection  dataset_api <- redcap_data(uri = "https://redcap.idibell.cat/api/",                            token = "55E5C3D1E83213ADA2182A4BFDEA") # This token is fictitious  }
